comments: Ross (ORL) brings his right forearm toward Diallo's (DET) path and marginal contact occurs with Diallo's front prior to his gather.

Anthony (ORL) establishes verticality as he retreats toward the baseline and absorbs the contact made with Diallo (DET) to his chest when Diallo cuts back from behind the backboard during the driving shot attempt.
Diallo (DET) tips the ball while it is outside of the imaginary cylinder above the rim.

Okeke's (ORL) right arm slightly extends outward as he turns to roll and marginal contact occurs with Joseph's (DET) face. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Lyles (DET) brings his hands forward and marginal contact occurs with Anthony's (ORL) front as Anthony drives toward the lane.
Diallo's (DET) left arm brushes Anthony's (ORL) front after his gather and marginal contact occurs.
Anthony (ORL) extends slightly toward Cunningham (DET) and marginal body contact occurs as Cunningham turns the corner during the drive.
Bey (DET) is moving toward Wagner (ORL) when marginal body contact occurs as Wagner retrieves the rebound.
Diallo (DET) extends and initiates contact with his left leg and lower body contact that affects Ross' (ORL) SQBR.
Joseph (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Harris' (ORL) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Ross (ORL) brushes Diallo's (DET) side during his upward motion and Diallo is able to move through the marginal contact to finish at the rim.
Joseph (DET) and Anthony (ORL) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Bey (DET) engages and disengages with Wagner (ORL) during the inbound.
Lyles (DET) and Okeke (ORL) engage and disengage with one another off ball.

Diallo (DET) brushes Ross' (ORL) left side and marginal contact occurs after Ross' gather. Cunningham (DET) jumps with his right forearm extended forward and he collapses his forearm as marginal contact occurs with Ross' front during the driving shot attempt.
Wagner (ORL) is moving forward as Diallo (DET) returns to the floor after receiving the pass and marginal contact occurs with Diallo's front.
Ross (ORL) legally contests Cunningham's (DET) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Bey (DET) and Anthony (ORL) extend for the rebound and each make clean contact with the ball as simultaneous incidental body contact occurs.
Wagner (ORL) establishes himself in a screening position in Diallo's (DET) path and does not deliver the contact as the switch takes place.
Bey (DET) legally contests Anthony's (ORL) jump shot attempt.
Joseph (DET) and Lyles (DET) each make incidental arm contact with Wagner (ORL) as Wagner mishandles the ball during rebounding.
Ross (ORL) commits a take foul on Joseph (DET).
